text: The Oakes Estate is located in Bloomfield, Essex County, New Jersey, United States. The building, designed by Charles Granville Jones was built in 1895,http://www.oakeside.org/mission.htm was added to the National Register of Historic Places on August 6, 1981. ==See also== *National Register of Historic Places listings in Essex County, New Jersey ==References== Category:Bloomfield, New Jersey Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in New Jersey Category:Queen Anne architecture in New Jersey Category:Colonial Revival architecture in New Jersey Category:Houses completed in 1895 Category:Houses in Essex County, New Jersey Category:National Register of Historic Places in Essex County, New Jersey Category:New Jersey Register of Historic Places
